      • copyTo

        void copyTo(int sourceIndex,
            byte[] destination,
            int destinationIndex,
            int length)
        Copies the bytes from the ByteString, starting at the specified position, to the specified position of the destination array. This method is actually a special case of System.arraycopy(java.lang.Object, int, java.lang.Object, int, int) which uses the ByteString as source.
        Parameters:
        sourceIndex - Starting position in the source ByteString.
        destination - The destination array.
        destinationIndex - Starting position in the destination data.
        length - Number of bytes that should be copied.
        Throws:
        IndexOutOfBoundsException - If copying would cause access of data outside array bounds.
